{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015kFU1Cjg7ZHUYzQGcdmftY","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Dallas W007 — Progression UI Implementation\n     2→\n     3→**Date:** 2026-03-13\n     4→**Task:** W007 — Implement Rebecca's progression UI design doc\n     5→**PR:** PR-4964594 (office-bohemia)\n     6→\n     7→## What I Learned\n     8→\n     9→1. **Bebop feature module pattern is strict and well-documented** — CONTRIBUTING.md has exhaustive rules for feature anatomy, atom conventions, and dependency flow. Following it exactly makes PRs clean.\n    10→\n    11→2. **CSS Modules in Bebop use `@layer component`** (not `@layer components` as I initially expected). The existing patterns show `@layer application` for layout-level styles and `@layer component` for individual component styles.\n    12→\n    13→3. **Jotai atom dispatch pattern** — The existing `chatModeAtoms.ts` uses action handler records mapping action types to state transforms. My progression atoms follow a switch-case variant that's equally valid but I could refactor to match the record pattern for consistency.\n    14→\n    15→4. **office-bohemia worktree setup requires `yarn install`** — Unlike smaller repos, the monorepo needs a full yarn install in each worktree (takes ~13 minutes). The `.yarn/install-state.gz` in the main tree doesn't transfer.\n    16→\n    17→5. **Test infrastructure requires `yarn build --to bebop`** first — Jest config depends on `@fluidx/office-bohemia-build-tools` which must be built before tests can run.\n    18→\n    19→6. **Phase 1 vs Phase 2 separation is clean** — The atom layer is the same for both phases. Only `useProgressionStream` needs to change when Sydney adds structured NDJSON progression events. This was a good design decision by Rebecca.\n    20→\n    21→## Patterns Established\n    22→\n    23→- `features/progression/` module following exact design doc structure\n    24→- Atom dispatch pattern with typed action unions\n    25→- CSS Module styling with `@layer component` and bebop design tokens (`--gnrc-*`, `--cplt-immutable-*`)\n    26→- Feature-level composition (no modifications to shared packages)\n    27→\n    28→## Gotchas\n    29→\n    30→- The cowork route (PR-4959092) needs to land before ProgressionCard can be visually tested in the app\n    31→- React Compiler means NO `useCallback`/`useMemo` — the compiler handles it\n    32→- Build times in office-bohemia are long (~10+ min for full build to bebop)\n    33→\n    34→## Next Steps\n    35→\n    36→- Wire ProgressionCard/UserQuestionBanner into cowork route message rendering\n    37→- Coordinate with Sydney team on structured progression NDJSON events\n    38→- Add feature flag gating before production ship\n    39→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9cb5a381-3127-41e9-8735-a531505f707f","uuid":"1536da52-4f7a-4c2d-a7cf-1dea7b0a9f87","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"C:\\Users\\yemishin\\.squad\\notes\\inbox\\dallas-W007-2026-03-13.md","content":"# Dallas W007 — Progression UI Implementation\n\n**Date:** 2026-03-13\n**Task:** W007 — Implement Rebecca's progression UI design doc\n**PR:** PR-4964594 (office-bohemia)\n\n## What I Learned\n\n1. **Bebop feature module pattern is strict and well-documented** — CONTRIBUTING.md has exhaustive rules for feature anatomy, atom conventions, and dependency flow. Following it exactly makes PRs clean.\n\n2. **CSS Modules in Bebop use `@layer component`** (not `@layer components` as I initially expected). The existing patterns show `@layer application` for layout-level styles and `@layer component` for individual component styles.\n\n3. **Jotai atom dispatch pattern** — The existing `chatModeAtoms.ts` uses action handler records mapping action types to state transforms. My progression atoms follow a switch-case variant that's equally valid but I could refactor to match the record pattern for consistency.\n\n4. **office-bohemia worktree setup requires `yarn install`** — Unlike smaller repos, the monorepo needs a full yarn install in each worktree (takes ~13 minutes). The `.yarn/install-state.gz` in the main tree doesn't transfer.\n\n5. **Test infrastructure requires `yarn build --to bebop`** first — Jest config depends on `@fluidx/office-bohemia-build-tools` which must be built before tests can run.\n\n6. **Phase 1 vs Phase 2 separation is clean** — The atom layer is the same for both phases. Only `useProgressionStream` needs to change when Sydney adds structured NDJSON progression events. This was a good design decision by Rebecca.\n\n## Patterns Established\n\n- `features/progression/` module following exact design doc structure\n- Atom dispatch pattern with typed action unions\n- CSS Module styling with `@layer component` and bebop design tokens (`--gnrc-*`, `--cplt-immutable-*`)\n- Feature-level composition (no modifications to shared packages)\n\n## Gotchas\n\n- The cowork route (PR-4959092) needs to land before ProgressionCard can be visually tested in the app\n- React Compiler means NO `useCallback`/`useMemo` — the compiler handles it\n- Build times in office-bohemia are long (~10+ min for full build to bebop)\n\n## Next Steps\n\n- Wire ProgressionCard/UserQuestionBanner into cowork route message rendering\n- Coordinate with Sydney team on structured progression NDJSON events\n- Add feature flag gating before production ship\n","numLines":39,"startLine":1,"totalLines":39}}}
