{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_018oWUXhn8qTeY6VNT6f2atH","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Dallas W009 — Implement Rebecca's Progression UI Design\n     2→\n     3→**Date:** 2026-03-13\n     4→**Task:** W009 — Implement Rebecca's design (Progression UI + Ask-User-Question)\n     5→**PR:** PR-4959092 (office-bohemia) — Updated existing cowork route PR\n     6→**Branch:** `dallas/add-cowork-route`\n     7→\n     8→## What Was Done\n     9→\n    10→Committed and pushed the Phase 1 (Option B) progression UI implementation that was built in W006 but never committed. Applied minor fixes:\n    11→- Added `focus-visible` states to skipButton and toggleButton for accessibility\n    12→- Removed unused `pulse` CSS keyframes and class (dead code)\n    13→- Removed unused `FC` type import from CoworkTranscript\n    14→\n    15→Updated PR-4959092 title, description, and posted implementation notes as ADO thread comment.\n    16→\n    17→## Key Learnings\n    18→\n    19→1. **Azure ADO MCP tools may not always be available** — When they're absent, use `git credential-manager get` to extract a Bearer token and call the ADO REST API directly via Node.js `https` module. The credential manager returns a JWT that works with Bearer auth.\n    20→\n    21→2. **Edit tool doesn't work across worktrees** — Files read from worktree paths (e.g., `C:/Users/yemishin/office-bohemia-cowork/...`) are not recognized by the Edit tool even after using Read. Workaround: use Node.js `fs` module to make edits in worktrees.\n    22→\n    23→3. **Python is not available on this DevBox** — Only Node.js (v24.11.0) is installed. Use `node -e` for scripting tasks instead of `python3 -c`.\n    24→\n    25→4. **Azure CLI (`az`) is broken on this DevBox** — It crashes with Python import errors. Cannot use `az devops` commands. Use REST API directly.\n    26→\n    27→5. **ADO PR REST API for office-bohemia:**\n    28→   - Repo ID: `74031860-e0cd-45a1-913f-10bbf3f82555`\n    29→   - Base URL: `https://office.visualstudio.com/DefaultCollection/OC/_apis/git/repositories/{repoId}`\n    30→   - PATCH `/pullrequests/{id}` to update title/description\n    31→   - POST `/pullrequests/{id}/threads` to create comment threads\n    32→   - GET `/pullrequests?searchCriteria.sourceRefName=refs/heads/{branch}` to find PRs by branch\n    33→\n    34→6. **Existing PR reuse** — When a branch already has an active PR, push additional commits to the same branch and update the PR title/description rather than creating a new PR.\n    35→\n    36→## Conventions Followed\n    37→\n    38→- Feature-first organization: `src/features/progression/`\n    39→- Jotai atoms (not Zustand) for local UI state\n    40→- CSS Modules with `@layer components` pattern\n    41→- `'use client'` directive on all client components\n    42→- Compose at feature level — no modifications to bebop-ux or bebop-conversation\n    43→- focus-visible states on all interactive buttons\n    44→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9cb5a381-3127-41e9-8735-a531505f707f","uuid":"2e72f4df-1fb0-44da-b0a9-4a23c0773d25","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"C:\\Users\\yemishin\\.squad\\notes\\inbox\\dallas-W009-2026-03-13.md","content":"# Dallas W009 — Implement Rebecca's Progression UI Design\n\n**Date:** 2026-03-13\n**Task:** W009 — Implement Rebecca's design (Progression UI + Ask-User-Question)\n**PR:** PR-4959092 (office-bohemia) — Updated existing cowork route PR\n**Branch:** `dallas/add-cowork-route`\n\n## What Was Done\n\nCommitted and pushed the Phase 1 (Option B) progression UI implementation that was built in W006 but never committed. Applied minor fixes:\n- Added `focus-visible` states to skipButton and toggleButton for accessibility\n- Removed unused `pulse` CSS keyframes and class (dead code)\n- Removed unused `FC` type import from CoworkTranscript\n\nUpdated PR-4959092 title, description, and posted implementation notes as ADO thread comment.\n\n## Key Learnings\n\n1. **Azure ADO MCP tools may not always be available** — When they're absent, use `git credential-manager get` to extract a Bearer token and call the ADO REST API directly via Node.js `https` module. The credential manager returns a JWT that works with Bearer auth.\n\n2. **Edit tool doesn't work across worktrees** — Files read from worktree paths (e.g., `C:/Users/yemishin/office-bohemia-cowork/...`) are not recognized by the Edit tool even after using Read. Workaround: use Node.js `fs` module to make edits in worktrees.\n\n3. **Python is not available on this DevBox** — Only Node.js (v24.11.0) is installed. Use `node -e` for scripting tasks instead of `python3 -c`.\n\n4. **Azure CLI (`az`) is broken on this DevBox** — It crashes with Python import errors. Cannot use `az devops` commands. Use REST API directly.\n\n5. **ADO PR REST API for office-bohemia:**\n   - Repo ID: `74031860-e0cd-45a1-913f-10bbf3f82555`\n   - Base URL: `https://office.visualstudio.com/DefaultCollection/OC/_apis/git/repositories/{repoId}`\n   - PATCH `/pullrequests/{id}` to update title/description\n   - POST `/pullrequests/{id}/threads` to create comment threads\n   - GET `/pullrequests?searchCriteria.sourceRefName=refs/heads/{branch}` to find PRs by branch\n\n6. **Existing PR reuse** — When a branch already has an active PR, push additional commits to the same branch and update the PR title/description rather than creating a new PR.\n\n## Conventions Followed\n\n- Feature-first organization: `src/features/progression/`\n- Jotai atoms (not Zustand) for local UI state\n- CSS Modules with `@layer components` pattern\n- `'use client'` directive on all client components\n- Compose at feature level — no modifications to bebop-ux or bebop-conversation\n- focus-visible states on all interactive buttons\n","numLines":44,"startLine":1,"totalLines":44}}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01BNBourgfACUV8E2z5dBoJf","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Dallas — Learnings from PR Status Sync\n     2→\n     3→**Date:** 2026-03-13\n     4→\n     5→## Key Learnings\n     6→\n     7→1. **Azure CLI (`az`) is broken on this DevBox** — DLL load failure for `win32file` in the `portalocker` module. All `az` commands fail, including `az repos pr show`. This affects both bash and PowerShell invocations.\n     8→\n     9→2. **Git credential manager is the reliable auth source** — Use `git credential fill` with `protocol=https` and `host=office.visualstudio.com` to get a bearer token (JWT). This works from bash but NOT from Node.js `execSync` (heredoc syntax issue on Windows).\n    10→\n    11→3. **ADO REST API PR status mapping:**\n    12→   - `status: \"active\"` = PR is open (maps to squad status `\"active\"`)\n    13→   - `mergeStatus: \"succeeded\"` = no merge conflicts, build passing -> `buildStatus: \"passing\"`\n    14→   - Reviewer `vote: 0` with at least one reviewer -> `reviewStatus: \"pending\"`\n    15→\n    16→4. **ADO PR reviewers are team groups, not individuals** — The office-bohemia repo auto-assigns team groups like `[TEAM FOUNDATION]\\Bebop PR Reviewers` and `[TEAM FOUNDATION]\\Bebop Bundle Size Approvers`.\n    17→\n    18→## Gotchas\n    19→\n    20→- **Never use `az` CLI on this machine** until the win32file DLL issue is resolved. Use `curl` + bearer token from git credential manager instead.\n    21→- **Node.js v24 on Windows** escapes `!==` in `-e` eval strings. Always write to a `.js` file instead of using inline eval.\n    22→- **heredoc (`<<<`) doesn't work in Windows cmd** — only works in bash/git-bash shell.\n    23→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9cb5a381-3127-41e9-8735-a531505f707f","uuid":"092a4757-ba39-454f-bf26-97fc49db7ced","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"C:\\Users\\yemishin\\.squad\\notes\\inbox\\dallas-2026-03-13.md","content":"# Dallas — Learnings from PR Status Sync\n\n**Date:** 2026-03-13\n\n## Key Learnings\n\n1. **Azure CLI (`az`) is broken on this DevBox** — DLL load failure for `win32file` in the `portalocker` module. All `az` commands fail, including `az repos pr show`. This affects both bash and PowerShell invocations.\n\n2. **Git credential manager is the reliable auth source** — Use `git credential fill` with `protocol=https` and `host=office.visualstudio.com` to get a bearer token (JWT). This works from bash but NOT from Node.js `execSync` (heredoc syntax issue on Windows).\n\n3. **ADO REST API PR status mapping:**\n   - `status: \"active\"` = PR is open (maps to squad status `\"active\"`)\n   - `mergeStatus: \"succeeded\"` = no merge conflicts, build passing -> `buildStatus: \"passing\"`\n   - Reviewer `vote: 0` with at least one reviewer -> `reviewStatus: \"pending\"`\n\n4. **ADO PR reviewers are team groups, not individuals** — The office-bohemia repo auto-assigns team groups like `[TEAM FOUNDATION]\\Bebop PR Reviewers` and `[TEAM FOUNDATION]\\Bebop Bundle Size Approvers`.\n\n## Gotchas\n\n- **Never use `az` CLI on this machine** until the win32file DLL issue is resolved. Use `curl` + bearer token from git credential manager instead.\n- **Node.js v24 on Windows** escapes `!==` in `-e` eval strings. Always write to a `.js` file instead of using inline eval.\n- **heredoc (`<<<`) doesn't work in Windows cmd** — only works in bash/git-bash shell.\n","numLines":23,"startLine":1,"totalLines":23}}}
