{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Y6phedi2r4uX4JRTigZBqq","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# CLAUDE.md\n     2→\n     3→This file provides guidance to Claude Code (claude.ai/code) when working with code in this repository.\n     4→\n     5→## Repository Overview\n     6→\n     7→Office-Bohemia is the primary repository for Microsoft Loop, built on the Fluid Framework for real-time collaboration. It's a Yarn-based monorepo (~200 packages) using Lage for task orchestration.\n     8→\n     9→## Documentation\n    10→\n    11→Detailed documentation lives in `./docs/`. Key sections:\n    12→\n    13→- `docs/developer-guide/` - Internal development docs\n    14→- `docs/partner-guide/` - For teams integrating with Loop\n    15→\n    16→## Documentation Ownership\n    17→\n    18→- This file defines **repo-wide** coding agent defaults.\n    19→- App/package-specific behavior should be documented in local docs in that scope.\n    20→- For Bebop work, see `apps/bebop/CLAUDE.md` (automatically includes agent workflow and architecture standards).\n    21→\n    22→## Common Commands\n    23→\n    24→All commands run from repo root. Use `yarn`, not `npm run`. Lage automatically handles prerequisites (build, bundle).\n    25→\n    26→```bash\n    27→# Development\n    28→yarn                              # Install dependencies (run after git pull or branch switch)\n    29→yarn start --to loop-app          # Start Loop app dev server\n    30→yarn build --to <package-name>    # Build up to a specific package\n    31→yarn test --to <package-name>     # Run unit tests\n    32→yarn test:e2e --to <package-name> # Run Playwright e2e tests\n    33→yarn prettier --to <package-name> # Format code\n    34→yarn lint --to <package-name>     # Lint package\n    35→yarn lint --fix --to <package-name> # Lint and auto-fix\n    36→\n    37→# Single test (from package directory)\n    38→yarn test TestFileName.test.ts\n    39→yarn test --testNamePattern \"pattern\"\n    40→yarn test:e2e --file TestFileName.playwright-test.ts\n    41→\n    42→# Faster builds for targeted work\n    43→yarn build --since master         # Only packages changed since master\n    44→yarn test --since master          # Test only changed packages\n    45→yarn build --scope <package-name> # Build package AND all its consumers\n    46→\n    47→# Validation\n    48→yarn validate                     # Full validation (build, lint, test, e2e)\n    49→yarn validate:lint                # Lint-only (faster)\n    50→\n    51→# Maintenance\n    52→yarn clean                        # Clean build artifacts\n    53→yarn scrub                        # Full clean including node_modules\n    54→yarn change                       # Generate change files for PRs\n    55→```\n    56→\n    57→Full script list in `package.json`. See `docs/developer-guide/tooling/yarn-script-reference.md` for details.\n    58→\n    59→### Claude Code Commands\n    60→\n    61→```bash\n    62→/review-branch                    # Review changes on current branch\n    63→/create-pr                        # Create PR for office-bohemia\n    64→```\n    65→\n    66→## Code Architecture\n    67→\n    68→### Directory Structure\n    69→\n    70→- `apps/` - Applications (loop-app, bebop, scriptor-pad, test-app)\n    71→- `packages/` - ~200 shared packages\n    72→- `tools/` - Build tooling\n    73→- `azure/` - Deployment configurations\n    74→- `docs/` - Engineering documentation\n    75→\n    76→### Core Architectural Concepts\n    77→\n    78→**Loop Components** are portable, collaborative experiences (LEAP: Live, Embeddable, Actionable, Portable). They render in any M365 host.\n    79→\n    80→**Loop Hosts** are applications that embed Loop Components (Teams, Outlook, Word, Loop App).\n    81→\n    82→**Containers** are Fluid Framework containers - the collaborative data layer. Key containers:\n    83→\n    84→- `loop-page-container` - Powers Loop pages (canvas with Scriptor, Tablero, etc.)\n    85→- `office-fluid-container` - Powers inline Loop components in Teams/Outlook chat\n    86→\n    87→**WorkspaceComponent** (`apps/loop-app/src/WorkspaceComponent/`) is the embedding surface for hosts to render full Loop workspace/page experiences. Hosts like the M365 Copilot App use this to embed Loop experiences without running the full Loop App. Served at `/workspaceComponentManifest.json`.\n    88→\n    89→### Key Packages\n    90→\n    91→| Package | Purpose |\n    92→|---------|---------|\n    93→| `loop-app` | Loop web application (apps/) |\n    94→| `loop-page-container` | Fluid container for Loop pages |\n    95→| `office-fluid-container` | Fluid container for inline components |\n    96→| `scriptor` | Rich text editing engine |\n    97→| `tablero` / `tablero-views` | Table component |\n    98→| `component-ux` | Shared UI components |\n    99→| `loop-app-ux` | Loop app specific UX |\n   100→| `base-container` | Container utilities |\n   101→\n   102→### Testing Container Changes\n   103→\n   104→- **For loop-page-container**: Use `yarn start --to loop-page-container` (demo app at localhost:3000)\n   105→- **For Loop App**: Use `yarn start --to loop-app`\n   106→- **For Teams/Outlook integration**: Use `yarn localDeploy --to loop-page-container` with Fiddler rules (see package README)\n   107→\n   108→**Important**: Loop App bundles loop-page-container. Avoid PRs that span both - this can cause compatibility issues with hosts loading containers from CDN.\n   109→\n   110→## Code Style Guidelines\n   111→\n   112→### TypeScript\n   113→\n   114→- No `as` type assertions, `any` types, or `!` non-null assertions\n   115→- Use `?.` and `??` over traditional null checks\n   116→- Prefer immutable data (`const`, `readonly`)\n   117→\n   118→### React\n   119→\n   120→- Components must be pure (same inputs = same output)\n   121→- `useEffect` only for external systems (APIs, subscriptions, timers) - always include cleanup\n   122→- Never use `useEffect` for derived state\n   123→- Group related state: `useState({ x: 0, y: 0 })`\n   124→- Use status enums over multiple booleans: `'loading' | 'error' | 'success'`\n   125→- Use `useId()` for accessible IDs for components\n   126→\n   127→### Async Code\n   128→\n   129→- Prefer `async/await` over callbacks/promises\n   130→- Use `Promise.all` for parallel execution\n   131→- Avoid `setTimeout` as workaround for race conditions\n   132→\n   133→### Logging\n   134→\n   135→- Use provided logger instance, not `console.log`\n   136→- Log specific fields, not entire objects\n   137→\n   138→### API Design\n   139→\n   140→- Don't break public package APIs\n   141→- Prefer private over public methods/properties\n   142→- Pass optional params as objects, not multiple optional parameters\n   143→\n   144→## Azure DevOps CLI Setup\n   145→\n   146→Many skills/commands use Azure CLI to interact with Azure DevOps. One-time setup:\n   147→\n   148→1. Install Azure CLI: <https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/cli/azure/install-azure-cli>\n   149→2. Log in: `az login` (do NOT use `--use-device-code` — not supported by this org)\n   150→3. The shared prereq script (`.claude/scripts/az-prereqs.sh`) handles extension installation and default configuration automatically.\n   151→\n   152→If commands fail with auth errors, run `az login` again (tokens expire after ~60 minutes).\n   153→\n   154→## Testing\n   155→\n   156→- Unit tests: `*.test.ts`\n   157→- Mock all external dependencies\n   158→- Use `jest.useFakeTimers()` instead of real timers\n   159→- E2E tests: `*.playwright-test.ts` - Playwright-based\n   160→- Live tests: `yarn test:e2e:live` - Tests against real endpoints (staging/dogfood/prod)\n   161→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9cb5a381-3127-41e9-8735-a531505f707f","uuid":"60946032-192c-43c6-981f-c06f05d73dea","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"C:/Users/yemishin/office-bohemia/CLAUDE.md","content":"# CLAUDE.md\n\nThis file provides guidance to Claude Code (claude.ai/code) when working with code in this repository.\n\n## Repository Overview\n\nOffice-Bohemia is the primary repository for Microsoft Loop, built on the Fluid Framework for real-time collaboration. It's a Yarn-based monorepo (~200 packages) using Lage for task orchestration.\n\n## Documentation\n\nDetailed documentation lives in `./docs/`. Key sections:\n\n- `docs/developer-guide/` - Internal development docs\n- `docs/partner-guide/` - For teams integrating with Loop\n\n## Documentation Ownership\n\n- This file defines **repo-wide** coding agent defaults.\n- App/package-specific behavior should be documented in local docs in that scope.\n- For Bebop work, see `apps/bebop/CLAUDE.md` (automatically includes agent workflow and architecture standards).\n\n## Common Commands\n\nAll commands run from repo root. Use `yarn`, not `npm run`. Lage automatically handles prerequisites (build, bundle).\n\n```bash\n# Development\nyarn                              # Install dependencies (run after git pull or branch switch)\nyarn start --to loop-app          # Start Loop app dev server\nyarn build --to <package-name>    # Build up to a specific package\nyarn test --to <package-name>     # Run unit tests\nyarn test:e2e --to <package-name> # Run Playwright e2e tests\nyarn prettier --to <package-name> # Format code\nyarn lint --to <package-name>     # Lint package\nyarn lint --fix --to <package-name> # Lint and auto-fix\n\n# Single test (from package directory)\nyarn test TestFileName.test.ts\nyarn test --testNamePattern \"pattern\"\nyarn test:e2e --file TestFileName.playwright-test.ts\n\n# Faster builds for targeted work\nyarn build --since master         # Only packages changed since master\nyarn test --since master          # Test only changed packages\nyarn build --scope <package-name> # Build package AND all its consumers\n\n# Validation\nyarn validate                     # Full validation (build, lint, test, e2e)\nyarn validate:lint                # Lint-only (faster)\n\n# Maintenance\nyarn clean                        # Clean build artifacts\nyarn scrub                        # Full clean including node_modules\nyarn change                       # Generate change files for PRs\n```\n\nFull script list in `package.json`. See `docs/developer-guide/tooling/yarn-script-reference.md` for details.\n\n### Claude Code Commands\n\n```bash\n/review-branch                    # Review changes on current branch\n/create-pr                        # Create PR for office-bohemia\n```\n\n## Code Architecture\n\n### Directory Structure\n\n- `apps/` - Applications (loop-app, bebop, scriptor-pad, test-app)\n- `packages/` - ~200 shared packages\n- `tools/` - Build tooling\n- `azure/` - Deployment configurations\n- `docs/` - Engineering documentation\n\n### Core Architectural Concepts\n\n**Loop Components** are portable, collaborative experiences (LEAP: Live, Embeddable, Actionable, Portable). They render in any M365 host.\n\n**Loop Hosts** are applications that embed Loop Components (Teams, Outlook, Word, Loop App).\n\n**Containers** are Fluid Framework containers - the collaborative data layer. Key containers:\n\n- `loop-page-container` - Powers Loop pages (canvas with Scriptor, Tablero, etc.)\n- `office-fluid-container` - Powers inline Loop components in Teams/Outlook chat\n\n**WorkspaceComponent** (`apps/loop-app/src/WorkspaceComponent/`) is the embedding surface for hosts to render full Loop workspace/page experiences. Hosts like the M365 Copilot App use this to embed Loop experiences without running the full Loop App. Served at `/workspaceComponentManifest.json`.\n\n### Key Packages\n\n| Package | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|\n| `loop-app` | Loop web application (apps/) |\n| `loop-page-container` | Fluid container for Loop pages |\n| `office-fluid-container` | Fluid container for inline components |\n| `scriptor` | Rich text editing engine |\n| `tablero` / `tablero-views` | Table component |\n| `component-ux` | Shared UI components |\n| `loop-app-ux` | Loop app specific UX |\n| `base-container` | Container utilities |\n\n### Testing Container Changes\n\n- **For loop-page-container**: Use `yarn start --to loop-page-container` (demo app at localhost:3000)\n- **For Loop App**: Use `yarn start --to loop-app`\n- **For Teams/Outlook integration**: Use `yarn localDeploy --to loop-page-container` with Fiddler rules (see package README)\n\n**Important**: Loop App bundles loop-page-container. Avoid PRs that span both - this can cause compatibility issues with hosts loading containers from CDN.\n\n## Code Style Guidelines\n\n### TypeScript\n\n- No `as` type assertions, `any` types, or `!` non-null assertions\n- Use `?.` and `??` over traditional null checks\n- Prefer immutable data (`const`, `readonly`)\n\n### React\n\n- Components must be pure (same inputs = same output)\n- `useEffect` only for external systems (APIs, subscriptions, timers) - always include cleanup\n- Never use `useEffect` for derived state\n- Group related state: `useState({ x: 0, y: 0 })`\n- Use status enums over multiple booleans: `'loading' | 'error' | 'success'`\n- Use `useId()` for accessible IDs for components\n\n### Async Code\n\n- Prefer `async/await` over callbacks/promises\n- Use `Promise.all` for parallel execution\n- Avoid `setTimeout` as workaround for race conditions\n\n### Logging\n\n- Use provided logger instance, not `console.log`\n- Log specific fields, not entire objects\n\n### API Design\n\n- Don't break public package APIs\n- Prefer private over public methods/properties\n- Pass optional params as objects, not multiple optional parameters\n\n## Azure DevOps CLI Setup\n\nMany skills/commands use Azure CLI to interact with Azure DevOps. One-time setup:\n\n1. Install Azure CLI: <https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/cli/azure/install-azure-cli>\n2. Log in: `az login` (do NOT use `--use-device-code` — not supported by this org)\n3. The shared prereq script (`.claude/scripts/az-prereqs.sh`) handles extension installation and default configuration automatically.\n\nIf commands fail with auth errors, run `az login` again (tokens expire after ~60 minutes).\n\n## Testing\n\n- Unit tests: `*.test.ts`\n- Mock all external dependencies\n- Use `jest.useFakeTimers()` instead of real timers\n- E2E tests: `*.playwright-test.ts` - Playwright-based\n- Live tests: `yarn test:e2e:live` - Tests against real endpoints (staging/dogfood/prod)\n","numLines":161,"startLine":1,"totalLines":161}}}
